- Junior.
- No, no. Just let him go.

38:52.797 --> 38:54.640
Let him go.

38:59.871 --> 39:02.784
Your dad called.

39:02.874 --> 39:06.344
He, uh... he said he wants you
to call him back to...

39:06.477 --> 39:08.787
discuss you coming
by the church today to...

39:08.880 --> 39:11.656
go over
your installation ceremony

39:11.783 --> 39:15.321
and the new construction
project.

39:15.453 --> 39:18.161
I don't know if I'm ready
to go back to work.

39:22.660 --> 39:25.834
I know you don't want
to hear this.

39:28.199 --> 39:31.043
We're all grieving.

39:31.169 --> 39:34.548
But we have to move on.

39:39.077 --> 39:42.991
Focusing back on the church
and your work,

39:43.081 --> 39:44.492
that's what you need.

39:48.319 --> 39:50.390
And, besides,
I already told him

39:50.521 --> 39:52.432
that you was gonna be there,
so...

39:52.557 --> 39:54.332
(both chuckle)

39:54.425 --> 39:56.905
(sniffles)

40:00.265 --> 40:03.838
Gonna check on...
check on Junior.

40:18.116 --> 40:21.097
(heart monitor
beeping rhythmically)

40:23.454 --> 40:25.434
Good morning.

40:26.791 --> 40:29.135
We saw Dr. Moore today.

40:29.260 --> 40:32.264
He says that your body's
accepting your new heart.

40:32.397 --> 40:34.377
You're gonna go home.

40:37.068 --> 40:40.208
This is God's work, baby.

40:40.305 --> 40:42.285
He is so good.

40:48.246 --> 40:50.226
(phone rings)

40:56.955 --> 40:58.332
Hello?

40:58.456 --> 40:59.833
BOYD:
Mr. Newman.

40:59.958 --> 41:01.665
This is Detective Boyd.

41:01.793 --> 41:04.399
I'm the lead detective handling
the case involving your son.

41:04.495 --> 41:05.906
Yes?

41:05.997 --> 41:08.238
First, let me express
my deepest condolences

41:08.333 --> 41:10.939
to you and your family
for your loss.

41:11.069 --> 41:13.982
Thank you.
How can I help you, Detective?

41:14.105 --> 41:15.812
I'm calling because
we now have evidence

41:15.940 --> 41:17.851
that we can charge a...

41:17.976 --> 41:21.685
Maria Hernandez
with vehicular manslaughter.

41:21.813 --> 41:23.690
Maria Hernandez?

41:23.815 --> 41:24.816
Yes, sir.

41:24.949 --> 41:26.360
That is the name of the minor

41:26.484 --> 41:29.465
that struck your son
while texting and driving.

41:30.822 --> 41:33.166
Where's she from?

41:33.291 --> 41:35.168
I'm sorry, sir,
but the subject is a minor,

41:35.293 --> 41:38.172
so at this point in time
all I can give you is a name.

41:38.296 --> 41:40.503
But the D.A. should
be contacting you soon.

41:41.933 --> 41:44.174
Can you at least
tell me her age?

41:44.302 --> 41:46.111
The subject was...

41:46.204 --> 41:49.208
17 years old at the time
of the incident.

41:49.340 --> 41:52.219
17. So young.

41:52.343 --> 41:54.323
Okay, I'm-I'm...

41:54.445 --> 41:56.550
I'm sorry, wha... what is she
being charged with?

41:56.681 --> 41:58.558
I thought it was
a traffic accident.

41:58.683 --> 42:02.187
The tragic death of your son
was a traffic accident.

42:02.320 --> 42:05.130
But, in this state, if we can
show criminal negligence,

42:05.223 --> 42:09.137
i.e. texting while operating
a motor vehicle, well,

42:09.227 --> 42:12.401
the charges of manslaughter
can be attached.

42:12.530 --> 42:14.703
So she could go to prison.

42:14.832 --> 42:16.709
Well, if the D.A.

42:16.834 --> 42:18.711
elects to charge her
as an adult...

42:18.836 --> 42:20.645
well, she'd be
a very old woman

42:20.738 --> 42:22.240
before she gets out.

42:22.373 --> 42:23.909
Oh.

42:24.042 --> 42:26.921
I guess I never thought
it could be so severe.

42:27.045 --> 42:28.922
Mr. Newman,

42:29.047 --> 42:31.391
you should be getting a call
from the D.A.'s office soon.

42:31.516 --> 42:34.395
And they can better
update you on your case.

42:34.519 --> 42:37.500
I thank you
for your time, sir.

42:37.588 --> 42:40.569
And, again...
my condolences.

42:40.691 --> 42:42.671
Thank you, Detective.

42:49.100 --> 42:51.171
FARNSWORTH: The programs
for the installation service

42:51.269 --> 42:54.011
go to the printers tomorrow.
David, if you would please,

42:54.105 --> 42:56.381
uh, make your
final changes tonight

42:56.507 --> 42:58.680
and give 'em to Brother Cecil
in the morning.

43:01.212 --> 43:02.520
David?

43:03.781 --> 43:05.283
Yeah. Yeah, sure.

43:05.416 --> 43:06.690
CECIL:
All right, well...

43:06.784 --> 43:08.195
that leaves on the agenda

43:08.286 --> 43:09.856
the new construction project.

43:09.954 --> 43:12.434
Well, the new
construction'll be David's

43:12.557 --> 43:14.230
first major project
as leader of this church.

43:14.358 --> 43:15.860
So I tell you what--

43:15.960 --> 43:18.600
we're gonna let him
make all future decisions.

43:18.729 --> 43:20.709
- All right, well...
- All right, y'all.

43:20.798 --> 43:22.106
David, we better to start
looking for new contractors,

43:22.233 --> 43:24.213
like, yesterday.

43:24.302 --> 43:26.282
One second, Cecil.

43:30.441 --> 43:32.284
Hey, Dad.

43:32.410 --> 43:34.321
What was that about?

43:34.445 --> 43:35.617
What do you mean?

43:35.746 --> 43:37.817
The new construction
was your idea.

43:37.949 --> 43:39.485
Now you're just gonna
walk away and leave it to me?

43:39.617 --> 43:42.120
Oh, son, you're taking over
this church in a month,

43:42.253 --> 43:43.926
and I have no doubt
in my mind

43:44.055 --> 43:46.831
that the new life center
will grow and flourish

43:46.958 --> 43:48.767
under your lead.
Besides,

43:48.893 --> 43:51.772
you've pretty much
been the lead on it anyhow.

43:51.896 --> 43:53.773
What...
You're just leaving?

43:53.898 --> 43:57.243
What about everything
that's happened?

43:57.335 --> 43:59.975
Proverbs 3:5 and 6--

44:00.104 --> 44:01.674
"Trust in the Lord
with all your heart

44:01.806 --> 44:04.446
"and lean not on your own
understanding.

44:04.575 --> 44:06.452
"In all your ways
acknowledge Him,

44:06.577 --> 44:08.284
and He will
set your paths straight."

44:08.412 --> 44:10.915
Proverbs.

44:11.015 --> 44:13.825
That's it? You're not
gonna answer the question?

44:16.254 --> 44:18.131
What happened to your son,
my grandson,

44:18.256 --> 44:20.497
was a tragic
and horrible thing,

44:20.625 --> 44:24.095
but the Lord's work
is still yet to be done.

44:24.195 --> 44:25.868
And no, son,
I'm not leaving you.

44:25.997 --> 44:28.876
I'm just going home.

44:42.113 --> 44:45.720
Lord, I know what Maria did
is a sin in Your eyes.

44:45.850 --> 44:48.296
But in her heart,

44:48.386 --> 44:50.127
in her soul,

44:50.221 --> 44:53.168
she is good.

44:53.291 --> 44:56.636
Lord, I ask that
You send us a blessing.

44:56.727 --> 44:59.537
Someone, anyone...

44:59.664 --> 45:01.473
to show the authorities

45:01.566 --> 45:04.046
all the good
that is in her.

45:06.971 --> 45:08.848
(hammering in distance)

45:08.973 --> 45:10.577
ED:
I'm sorry, John.

45:10.708 --> 45:12.381
I just don't have room
or the work

45:12.510 --> 45:14.581
to bring on your team
right now.

45:14.712 --> 45:18.182
I've always been there
for you, Ed.

45:19.550 --> 45:21.860
I wish there was
something I could do.

45:21.986 --> 45:24.091
My father started
Danielson Construction

45:24.222 --> 45:25.826
40 years ago.

45:25.923 --> 45:27.368
We invested
every penny he made

45:27.491 --> 45:29.027
back into the company.

45:29.160 --> 45:32.198
Hired quality workers.

45:32.330 --> 45:34.037
But today all these guys
have to do is rely on

45:34.165 --> 45:35.508
some government regulation.

45:35.600 --> 45:37.409
- That's not true, John.
- No, that is true.

45:37.535 --> 45:38.605
How many of your men

45:38.736 --> 45:40.443
actually earned a spot
on your team?

45:41.839 --> 45:43.216
How many
belong in this country?

45:43.341 --> 45:46.220
Every last one of them!

45:46.344 --> 45:48.722
You want to know why no one
returns your calls, John?

45:50.214 --> 45:51.284
It's you.

45:51.415 --> 45:54.055
You're always angry
about something.

45:54.185 --> 45:57.462
And you always blame others
for your problems.

45:57.588 --> 46:00.592
You have a lot
to be thankful for, son.

46:00.725 --> 46:03.365
I've got a lot
to be thankful for?

46:03.461 --> 46:06.533
I'm filing for bankruptcy
in four weeks.

46:06.631 --> 46:10.443
Your daughter
just received a new heart.

46:10.568 --> 46:13.139
Do you not see that as nothing
less than a blessing from God

46:13.271 --> 46:15.148
and a reason for prayer?

46:15.273 --> 46:17.719
Are you actually gonna
stand there and tell me

46:17.808 --> 46:19.287
that the reason
your business is flourishing

46:19.410 --> 46:20.946
is because you pray?

46:21.078 --> 46:23.558
That's exactly what
I'm standing here doing.

46:23.648 --> 46:27.118
God tells us if we ask,
it will be given to us.

46:27.251 --> 46:28.992
I pray for God's blessings

46:29.120 --> 46:31.896
and mercy every day, son.

46:37.428 --> 46:39.931
I'm giving you the name
of a very good friend.

46:40.064 --> 46:42.237
He's adding a major addition
to his church.

46:42.333 --> 46:44.244
It's a really big project.

46:44.335 --> 46:48.147
I'm stretched thin right now--
I'm not bidding the job.

46:48.272 --> 46:50.149
That's all I can do for you.

46:53.010 --> 46:54.990
Thanks.

46:56.347 --> 46:58.827
John.

46:58.949 --> 47:00.951
Give him a call.

47:01.085 --> 47:04.623
And when you go interview...

47:04.755 --> 47:07.201
leave your anger
in the truck.

47:15.266 --> 47:17.439
Children's center right there.

47:17.535 --> 47:19.481
Yeah, that-that's a good spot
for that playground wing

47:19.603 --> 47:21.480
-you were talking about.
- Mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

47:21.605 --> 47:23.551
- I think this is...
- Oh. Okay.

47:30.881 --> 47:33.384
CECIL:
Hey, Mr. Danielson, right?

47:33.517 --> 47:34.962
I'm Cecil King.

47:35.052 --> 47:36.531
Wasn't really expecting
a building this nice

47:36.654 --> 47:38.497
in this area.

47:38.622 --> 47:41.159
Well, God's been good.
He's been good.

47:41.292 --> 47:43.670
So, let me... let me
introduce you to Pastor.

47:43.794 --> 47:45.501
We're just back here
going over some things.

47:45.629 --> 47:47.506
He'll be able
to make it clear to you--

47:47.631 --> 47:50.703
you know, what his vision is
and direction he's headed.

47:50.835 --> 47:53.714
Mr. Danielson, Pastor Newman.
Thanks for coming out.

47:53.838 --> 47:56.546
Doesn't really look like you
need any work done around here.

47:56.674 --> 47:59.177
What is it you're looking
to get done'?

47:59.310 --> 48:03.019
Okay. A man who likes
to dive right in.

48:03.147 --> 48:05.058
Well, our plans
are to build out

48:05.182 --> 48:07.093
this whole staked-off
area here.

48:07.218 --> 48:09.323
And maybe add
an addition right here

48:09.420 --> 48:11.331
for our children's center.

48:11.422 --> 48:12.924
That's a pretty big job.

48:13.057 --> 48:15.537
- Yeah.
- Gonna be expensive.

48:15.659 --> 48:18.105
I would have to see proof of
funds before we get started,

48:18.229 --> 48:21.438
because, honestly...
I can't waste my time.

48:21.565 --> 48:23.238
We would n”:
call you out here

48:23.367 --> 48:25.506
to waste your time,
Mr. Danielson.

48:25.603 --> 48:29.380
But only if we offer you
the job will we show you

48:29.507 --> 48:32.954
any documentation
or proof of funds.

48:33.077 --> 48:34.454
CECIL:
Which, at that point,

48:34.578 --> 48:36.057
you'll be dealing with me.

48:36.180 --> 48:38.126
And I can assure you
we got everything we need.

48:42.353 --> 48:44.629
I'm probably
not the man for this.

48:44.755 --> 48:46.894
What do you mean?
Wait a minute.

48:47.024 --> 48:48.401
- Let me...
- Cecil, Cecil.

48:48.526 --> 48:50.938
Pastor, he's the last one
on the list.

48:51.061 --> 48:54.201
- Let him go.
-(truck engine starts)

48:54.298 --> 48:56.209
DAVID: <i>What do you mean
he's not here?</i>

48:56.300 --> 49:00.077
He left a note saying that
he was going for a bike ride.

49:02.540 --> 49:04.417
He knows he can't
just leave the house

49:04.542 --> 49:06.146
without letting us know.
And what about church?

49:06.277 --> 49:08.587
He knew we were
going to church today.

49:08.712 --> 49:10.988
He needs time.

49:11.115 --> 49:13.095
He needs space.

49:15.286 --> 49:17.391
<i>N'</i>

49:17.488 --> 49:19.092
FARNSWORTH:
And how do <i>I</i> know

49:19.223 --> 49:20.998
<i>there's a place in heaven?</i>

49:21.125 --> 49:22.729
Because scripture tells us

49:22.827 --> 49:26.604
that in our "Father's house
there are many rooms.

49:26.730 --> 49:29.233
"If it were not so,
would I have told you

49:29.333 --> 49:31.939
"that I am going
to prepare a place for you?

49:32.069 --> 49:34.174
"And if I go and prepare
a place for you,

49:34.305 --> 49:38.014
"I will come back and welcome
you into My presence,

49:38.142 --> 49:41.521
so you also
may be where I am."

